title: Geneseo Fire Protection District RFP for Dual Band Portable 700/800 VHF STARCOM Radios

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Puerto Rico public records law, I hereby request the following records:

All documents, proposals, and related submissions provided to the Geneseo Fire Protection District in response to the solicitation R-20250818-1081 for Dual Band Portable 700/800 VHF STARCOM Radios, published on August 15, 2025.

Specifically, please provide any and all proposals, bids, supporting documents, correspondence, or evaluation materials submitted by vendors or respondents for this RFP.

If any portion of the requested records is withheld due to statutory exemptions, please specify the exact exemption and provide the remaining non-exempt records.

Please provide the documents in electronic format if available. I appreciate your timely response in accordance with the FOIA statutory deadline.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Michael Tillman

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Emails, text messages and Microsoft Teams messages sent and/or received by CM Nelson, CM Saka CM Hollingsworth, CM Rivera, CM Juarez, or CM Kettle on 9/9 from 1pm to 5pm, including any accompanying attachments and associated metadata. For text messages and Teams messages, please include messages sent/received in chats 30 minutes before or after responsive messages for context.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse
